122
00:05:17,640 --> 00:05:22,080
Just what are your thoughts on just consciousness?

123
00:05:22,080 --> 00:05:23,720
I haven't seen the word in this book.

124
00:05:23,720 --> 00:05:26,920
Maybe if you wrote about it, maybe you haven't.

125
00:05:26,920 --> 00:05:30,760
But physicists have a lot to say about consciousness.

126
00:05:30,760 --> 00:05:33,840
And idealists have a lot to say about consciousness.

127
00:05:33,840 --> 00:05:37,120
But I haven't heard Wolfgang say anything about consciousness.

128
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:39,520
Is there anything you'd like to personally

129
00:05:39,520 --> 00:05:44,160
or professionally say about that topic?

130
00:05:44,160 --> 00:05:49,160
Well, I think the topic of consciousness

131
00:05:49,160 --> 00:05:54,520
is obviously very central, very major.

132
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:58,960
And what I have to say about it, I think,

133
00:05:58,960 --> 00:06:06,320
can best be described as being the very opposite of what

134
00:06:06,320 --> 00:06:14,920
is nowadays involved regarding the subject of consciousness.

135
00:06:14,920 --> 00:06:25,480
Because I am persuaded that instead of coming somehow

136
00:06:25,480 --> 00:06:32,920
up from the bottom by some process of evolution,

137
00:06:32,920 --> 00:06:37,080
consciousness is ultimately, in the final count,

138
00:06:37,080 --> 00:06:41,280
what used to be called a Norman day.

139
00:06:41,280 --> 00:06:46,520
It is actually rooted in divinity itself.

140
00:06:46,520 --> 00:06:51,680
And by way of explication, let me mention

141
00:06:51,680 --> 00:06:58,400
that the oldest tradition, intellectual tradition

142
00:06:58,400 --> 00:07:02,040
in the world unquestionably is a Vedic.

143
00:07:02,040 --> 00:07:05,920
And in the Vedic tradition, consciousness

144
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:08,840
is indeed a Norman day.

145
00:07:08,840 --> 00:07:16,400
And it is part of the Sanskrit word satchitananda.

146
00:07:16,400 --> 00:07:23,400
So satchitananda, these are three words put into one.

147
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:26,560
Sat means being.

148
00:07:26,560 --> 00:07:29,920
Chit means consciousness.

149
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:33,400
And ananda means bliss.

150
00:07:33,400 --> 00:07:40,120
So being consciousness and bliss are, so to speak,

151
00:07:40,120 --> 00:07:44,160
the three aspects or faces, if you will,

152
00:07:44,160 --> 00:07:48,320
of the divinity, the very, very first principle.

153
00:07:48,320 --> 00:07:55,160
And I honestly believe that there is no other way

154
00:07:55,160 --> 00:07:58,120
of really understanding consciousness.

155
00:07:58,120 --> 00:08:00,000
It's not an epiphenomenon.

156
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:04,960
It has nothing whatsoever to do with neurons.

157
00:08:04,960 --> 00:08:09,960
And in fact, it is rooted in the very, very first principle

158
00:08:09,960 --> 00:08:11,720
of all, which is God.

159
00:08:14,360 --> 00:08:21,760
So I think these remarks may suffice

160
00:08:21,760 --> 00:08:27,920
to show that my thinking is really very far removed

161
00:08:27,920 --> 00:08:32,400
from the contemporary, because the contemporary thinking

162
00:08:32,400 --> 00:08:36,680
is characterized by the fact that almost instinctively,

163
00:08:36,680 --> 00:08:42,440
contemporary Western man wants to understand everything

164
00:08:42,440 --> 00:08:48,560
from the bottom, which he conceives more or less

165
00:08:48,560 --> 00:08:52,880
in terms of quantum mechanics.

166
00:08:52,880 --> 00:08:59,280
And this is, to me, the epitome of error.

167
00:08:59,280 --> 00:09:04,000
And in fact, I would justify this claim

168
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:12,600
by pointing out that the contemporary metaphysics is

169
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:17,200
really nothing new, but it is a revival

170
00:09:17,240 --> 00:09:23,360
of the philosophy of Democritus, who famously

171
00:09:23,360 --> 00:09:37,600
said the Golger believed in qualities, color,

172
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:40,320
the sweet and the bitter.

173
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:45,920
But in reality, there is only atoms and the void.

174
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:54,440
So this is basically not only one

175
00:09:54,440 --> 00:09:58,560
of the oldest philosophical positions of mankind,

176
00:09:58,560 --> 00:10:03,520
but it has been revived in the 17th century,

177
00:10:03,520 --> 00:10:08,520
and it has become our modern cradle.

178
00:10:08,520 --> 00:10:14,480
And let me mention that very soon after Democritus

179
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:21,200
propounded his theory concerning atoms and the void,

180
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:29,840
Plato attacked it, and I believe rigorously disqualified

181
00:10:29,840 --> 00:10:33,440
this position once and for all.

182
00:10:33,440 --> 00:10:37,960
And so for 2,000 years thereafter,

183
00:10:37,960 --> 00:10:45,800
the well-informed regarded this atomistic metaphysics

184
00:10:45,800 --> 00:10:47,760
as a heresy.

185
00:10:47,760 --> 00:10:52,080
And so what happened in the 17th century

186
00:10:52,080 --> 00:10:58,640
under the aegis of people like Descartes and Galileo,

187
00:10:58,640 --> 00:11:05,880
that ancient heresy was revived and became

188
00:11:05,880 --> 00:11:12,320
the foundation of what we nowadays call the Enlightenment.

189
00:11:12,320 --> 00:11:21,720
So this is, so to speak, the historical overview of where

190
00:11:21,720 --> 00:11:25,400
we find ourselves today.

191
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:31,920
And needless to say, I have been an opponent

192
00:11:31,920 --> 00:11:40,720
of the current Weltanschauung since the age of 14, really.

193
00:11:40,720 --> 00:11:43,800
Really, what happened when you were 14?

194
00:11:43,800 --> 00:11:46,680
That made that happen?

195
00:11:46,680 --> 00:11:51,960
Well, I think the decisive event was that somehow or other,

196
00:11:51,960 --> 00:11:56,600
I came across a very important book,

197
00:11:56,600 --> 00:12:02,160
a book by Alfred North Whitehead entitled

198
00:12:02,160 --> 00:12:05,520
Science in the Modern World.

199
00:12:05,520 --> 00:12:07,920
I read this book with great interest.

200
00:12:07,920 --> 00:12:15,040
I don't think I understood that much because I was very young.

201
00:12:15,040 --> 00:12:23,800
But I understood enough to be fascinated and, in a sense,

202
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:30,720
to be devoted to these questions for the rest of my life.

203
00:12:34,200 --> 00:12:41,960
So Whitehead, as it were, awakened my philosophical interest

204
00:12:41,960 --> 00:12:47,000
and instincts, if you will, instinctively

205
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:51,600
when I read about the fallacy of misplaced concreteness

206
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:55,640
and these things, I realized that this must be true.

207
00:12:58,200 --> 00:13:05,560
And so this started me on a career which

208
00:13:05,560 --> 00:13:09,000
put me in the position of the outsider

209
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:13,240
from the very beginning.

210
00:13:13,240 --> 00:13:16,240
I always felt myself as an outsider

211
00:13:16,240 --> 00:13:19,520
in the contemporary Western culture.

212
00:13:19,520 --> 00:13:24,280
And the reason was that I felt myself as an insider

213
00:13:24,280 --> 00:13:30,240
when it comes to the ancient philosophies, primarily

214
00:13:30,240 --> 00:13:32,720
Platonism.

215
00:13:32,720 --> 00:13:37,920
So in Platonism, I felt that I was an insider.

216
00:13:37,920 --> 00:13:39,960
Not that I understood it that well,

217
00:13:39,960 --> 00:13:44,000
but instinctively I was drawn to it.

218
00:13:44,080 --> 00:13:50,440
And something within me assured me

219
00:13:50,440 --> 00:13:53,720
that this must be the truth.

220
00:13:53,720 --> 00:14:00,400
And incidentally, Platonism doesn't stand alone.

221
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:08,280
It is inherently the same as the Vedic tradition.

222
00:14:08,280 --> 00:14:11,160
There are certain differences.

223
00:14:11,160 --> 00:14:13,600
But in essence, it is the same doctrine.

224
00:14:16,160 --> 00:14:27,760
And as I said, the contemporary Weltanschauung,

225
00:14:27,760 --> 00:14:32,400
which is regards particles of some kind or another

226
00:14:32,400 --> 00:14:38,320
as a very basis from which everything else evolves,

227
00:14:38,320 --> 00:14:47,480
that Weltanschauung is really nothing new at all.

228
00:14:47,480 --> 00:14:50,680
As I said, it goes back to the Democritus.

229
00:14:50,680 --> 00:14:53,720
And you might say it is one of the oldest heresies

230
00:14:53,720 --> 00:14:56,520
in the history of human thought.

231
00:14:56,520 --> 00:14:58,800
You're not a fan of atomistic thinking.

232
00:14:58,800 --> 00:15:02,880
That's certainly what I got it from reading your book.

233
00:15:02,880 --> 00:15:09,080
And you even go as far as to say that there are no,

234
00:15:09,080 --> 00:15:10,560
that particles do not exist.

235
00:15:14,840 --> 00:15:23,280
Yes, when you really pursue the Platonist metaphysics

236
00:15:23,280 --> 00:15:32,440
and apply it to the contemporary panorama of physics

237
00:15:32,520 --> 00:15:35,720
with its division between classical physics and quantum

238
00:15:35,720 --> 00:15:44,200
physics, you find, and this came to me as an amazement,

239
00:15:44,200 --> 00:15:49,880
you find that everything falls into place.

240
00:15:49,880 --> 00:15:53,960
And you can, in fact, understand this division

241
00:15:53,960 --> 00:15:58,760
between classical physics and quantum physics

242
00:15:58,760 --> 00:16:05,080
in a brand new way, which finally makes sense.

243
00:16:05,080 --> 00:16:07,800
I really like you to go deeper into that,

244
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:12,320
or at least explain your solution to this problem.

245
00:16:12,320 --> 00:16:16,240
So if you can briefly state the problem,

246
00:16:16,240 --> 00:16:17,320
and then your solution.

247
00:16:21,560 --> 00:16:27,480
Yes, let me just say by way of introduction

248
00:16:27,480 --> 00:16:33,680
that the Platonist metaphysics is, in a sense,

249
00:16:33,680 --> 00:16:41,400
the diametric opposite of what contemporary intellectuals

250
00:16:41,400 --> 00:16:47,080
believe, because contemporary intellectuals

251
00:16:47,080 --> 00:16:52,440
believe that it all begins with atoms.

252
00:16:53,440 --> 00:17:00,840
Nowadays, this is conceived evidently in quantum mechanical terms,

253
00:17:00,840 --> 00:17:07,240
but metaphysically speaking, it's just atoms and the void,

254
00:17:07,240 --> 00:17:12,840
very much as the democratus conceived of it.

255
00:17:12,840 --> 00:17:18,240
It's the beginning of the fifth century BC.

256
00:17:19,240 --> 00:17:25,520
So in a sense, you can say there's nothing new under the sun,

257
00:17:25,520 --> 00:17:31,400
because stripped of its technical aspects,

258
00:17:31,400 --> 00:17:37,280
the contemporary worldview is basically

259
00:17:37,280 --> 00:17:40,160
democratus all over again.

260
00:17:40,200 --> 00:17:49,800
And it is as much a heresy today as it was in the early days

261
00:17:49,800 --> 00:17:51,640
of democratus.

